# SuperHouse | UT61e Web UI

Simple Node to output a Web UI for the Uni-Trends UT61e multimeter using the [UT61e Wifi to MQTT board](https://www.superhouse.tv/product/ut61e-multimeter-wifi-interface/) created by Jonathan Oxer [@SuperHouse](https://www.superhouse.tv/).

---

## Configuration

### MQTT In Node
Connect an "MQTT In" Node ensuring you configure your MQTT Broker and Topic e.g.

` tele/ut61e/json`
 
>  Note: UT61e Web UI expects the JSON Topic provided by the UT61e Wifi to MQTT board library.

### SuperHouse | UT61e UI Node
Configure the "SuperHouse | UT61e UI" Node by ensuring your Node Red Host is correctly entered e.g. (nodered.local or 192.168.1.50).

> Note: Do not include the port.

You are able to customise the Web UI URL by default this is set to `<your-node-red-host/>ut61e` e.g.http://nodered.local/ut61e

---

## Expected JSON Format:

`{"currentType":"DC","unit":"V","value":"24.318","negative":false}`

---
